# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the code is
#   intended to run in multiple environments; otherwise, check them in:
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if delegates want to install dependency from Pipfile,
#   and build from shared Pipfile.lock, then commit it.
#   Otherwise, ignore it:
# Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipenv, poetry.lock is generally committed, but can be ignored if desired.
# poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipenv, pdm.lock is generally committed, but can be ignored if desired.
# pdm.lock

# PEP 582; project local packages directory (used by pdm)
